ARGUMENT.

Disdaining the court’s or kings complainings, Fate has carried away Moray ere his time. After the removal of that star, Fullerton was drowned in Lethe's untimely surge. Let Lachesis rage at will: alter such sad deaths, nor court nor king can mourn.
